strings:
<se_low>Yangus: I was well narked to find the casino shut
the first time I come 'ere.
I'd been lookin' forward to a few games.
<se_low>Yangus: It was almost as bad as the time I found out a wallet I'd nicked only 'ad two measly gold coins in it!
<se_low>Yangus: Crikey! I've just remembered!
<se_low>Yangus: We was s'posed to be goin' to that Dragon Graveyard place to 'elp that Cash geezer.

<se_low>Yangus: ‘Duty and 'umanity’, that's my motto.
I just forgot the duty part this time...

<se_low>Yangus: I ain't too 'appy about still bein' 'ere.
I mean, it ain't manners to keep people waitin'.
An' I'm big on manners, I am.
<se_low>Yangus: Crikey! I've just remembered!
<se_low>Yangus: We was s'posed to be goin' to that Dragon Graveyard place to 'elp that Carrie girl.

<se_low>Yangus: ‘Duty and 'umanity’, that's my motto.
I just forgot the duty part this time...

<se_low>Yangus: I ain't too 'appy about still bein' 'ere.
I mean, it ain't manners to keep people waitin'.
An' I'm big on manners, I am.
<se_low>Yangus: We should go an' let our 'air down in the casino one more time before we go off an' fight Rhapthorne. Not that I've got that much to let down, but still...
<se_low>Yangus: Wiv a bit o' luck, we might win a decent stack o' tokens. Then we can go off into battle knowin' we've got a bit o' good fortune on our side!
<se_low>Yangus: A bit of a boost like that'll do us no end o' good. We'll make easy work of 'im!
<se_low>Yangus: It can't be good when there's monsters comin' inta town, eh? I doubt they're very relaxin' to 'ave around.
<se_low>Yangus: Bet this is all cos o' that Lord o' Darkness an' all.
<se_high>Jessica: Now that I think about it, Rhapthorne must be behind the murder of Golding, too.
<se_high>Jessica: At the time, I thought Dhoulmagus was just on a mindless killing spree.
<se_high>Jessica: I'm picturing Cash waiting for us all alone under the scorching desert sun...
<se_high>Jessica: Oooh...!
<se_high>Jessica: Wow! Now I feel guilty...
<se_high>Jessica: I'm picturing Carrie waiting for us all alone under the scorching desert sun...
<se_high>Jessica: Oooh...!
<se_high>Jessica: Wow! Now I feel guilty...
<se_high>Jessica: Seeing the casino up and running again makes me realise how much Cash and Carrie have grown up.
<se_high>Jessica: I wonder if other towns and castles are having the same problem with monsters coming in?

<se_def>Angelo: I wouldn't be surprised.<page>Angelo: Ever since Rhapthorne was resurrected,
the monsters have been getting stronger and stronger. This could probably happen anywhere.
<se_low>Yangus: I bet it's 'im who's gettin' 'em all to go on the rampage.
<se_def>Angelo: No, I don't think so. He doesn't seem to have any followers. He's hardly the kind of guy you'd want to be around.
<se_high>Jessica: I wonder if that king squid was actually sent here by Rhapthorne? You know, like an assassin?
<se_high>Jessica: Actually, thinking about it, I can't imagine Rhapthorne needing a squid's help. He seems to have the whole assassination thing nailed.
<se_def>Angelo: If only we could've saved Golding...or some[-]body...anybody...from Rhapthorne's evil grasp...
<se_def>Angelo: Then he'd never have been resurrected and we wouldn't have had all this bother trying to save the world.
<se_def>Angelo: Oh yeah. Cash and Carrie are having that crazy trial of theirs to decide who takes over the casino.
<se_def>Angelo: Weren't we supposed to go along as Cash's bodyguards? I'd completely forgotten. Oh well. He's a big boy.
<se_def>Angelo: Oh yeah. Cash and Carrie are having that crazy trial of theirs to decide who takes over the casino.

<se_def>Angelo: Weren't we supposed to go along as Carrie's bodyguards? I'd completely forgotten.
It's not like me to keep a lady waiting.

<se_def>Angelo: The end of the world is upon us!
But no one seems to be all that bothered.
<se_def>Angelo: I suppose a burning red sky just isn't exciting enough to tear them away from a good old game of bingo!
<se_def>Angelo: Those people we saw fighting that king squid seemed a bit scared of Cash and Carrie, don't you think?

<se_def>Angelo: Not that I blame them. That pair would be a nightmare to work for, I'm sure.
Not like our very own King Troll! Ha hah!
<se_low>Yangus: It'd be quicker to give the old echo flute a ‘Toot-oot-ot! ♪’ rather than askin' about town.
<se_low>Yangus: If we don't 'urry up an' find them seven orbs, Rhapthorne's gonna cause all kinds o' bother!
<se_high>Jessica: According to Empyrea, the only way to defeat Rhapthorne is by collecting orbs that contain the power of the great sages.
<se_high>Jessica: I suppose that means the seven great sages will be together again, just like in the old legends. But this time, they'll be in the form of orbs.
<se_def>Angelo: Empyrea's not very helpful, is she? The least she could've done was collect these orbs for us.
<se_def>Angelo: Oh! This is turning into quite a chore.
<se_low>Yangus: That's it! Did you 'ear that noise!? That means there must be an orb 'ere!

<se_high>Jessica: There must be an orb nearby!
Come on, let's look around!
<se_def>Angelo: Bingo! Nice one. That was pretty impressive.
<se_def>Angelo: Now let's get that orb!
<se_high>Red: So at the end o' the day, it was Rhapthorne wot caused the casino to close down. Blimey, d'ya think 'e's got it in for gamblers? Brrr, I 'ope not!
<se_high>Red: ...Didn't Cash an' Carrie say summat about us 'elpin' out wiv some 'ead-to-'ead they was gonna do?
<se_high>Red: I 'ope they ain't waitin' for us already, eh?
<se_high>Red: ...Didn't Cash an' Carrie say summat about us 'elpin' out wiv some 'ead-to-'ead they was gonna do?
<se_high>Red: I 'ope they ain't waitin' for us already, eh?
<se_high>Red: Yer luck's in, is it? That's why yer 'ittin' the casino? ...Well if yer luck's in, shouldn't we be usin' it to see off Rhapthorne? Wot are ya gonna do if ya use it all up, eh?
<se_high>Red: Honestly, sometimes I think you ain't got a flamin' clue, <hero>, I really do!

<se_high>Red: Wot I wanna know is, 'ow did a king squid
end up in the town's fountain anyway, eh?
Walked 'ere, did it? From the coast?
<se_high>Red: Must've been a pretty determined thing, wotever.
<se_low>Morrie: Signor Golding, the proprietario of the casino, he used to take part in the Monster Arena.
<se_low>Morrie: He was a very busy man, so he was not coming for some times. But I still cannot believe he is defunct. It is a terribile news.
<se_low>Morrie: The child of signor Golding was asking us to be the guardie, no? Why we are not going?
<se_low>Morrie: Ragazzo! A man must never go back on a promessa to another man!
<se_low>Morrie: We must find him and say scusi, ay?
<se_low>Morrie: The child of signor Golding was asking us to be the guardie, no? Why we are not going?
<se_low>Morrie: Ragazzo! A man must never go back on a promessa to another man!
<se_low>Morrie: We must find him and say scusi, ay?
<se_high>Jessica: Um...Morrie...Carrie's a girl.
